The anapaest is never put after a tribraoh or daetyl and is used less often in the even than in the odd feet, while neither anapaest nor tribrech is frequent in the 4th; in- deed trisyllabis feet generally ere more sparingly used than in senarii.

At the end of the 4th foot there is a division of the verse, called in this instance diaeresis (διαίρεσις ‘division’); the ah foot should consequently end with the end of a word, but the rule is often neglected.
